    <!-- Why is Thila Homam performed? -->
    <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h4 class="card-title">Why is Thila Homam Performed in Rameswaram?</h4>
        <p class="card-text">
          Rameswaram is considered one of the most sacred places to perform Thila Homam. It is one of the 12 Jyotirlingas and holds immense spiritual power. Performing the ritual here offers strong relief from <strong>Pitru Dosha</strong> by appeasing one's ancestors.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sudden death in family with no reason</li>
          <li>Trouble in married life</li>
          <li>Delay in property settlements or legal issues</li>
          <li>Unexplained financial loss or job delays</li>
          <li>Lack of peace or frequent conflicts in the family</li>
          <li>Delay in childbirth</li>
          <li>Brings peace to ancestral souls</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

 

    <!-- When should I perform? -->
    <div class="card mb-4 shadow-sm">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h4 class="card-title">When Should I Perform Thila Homam?</h4>
        <p class="card-text">
          Thila Homam can be performed on <strong>any day in Rameswaram</strong>. However, it is especially powerful on <strong>Amavasya (New Moon Day)</strong>. The duration depends on chant count, typically lasting <strong>around 3 hours</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

